Dr. Martin Salia, a general surgeon who dedicated his life to saving others, has passed away from Ebola at the University of Nebraska Medical Center. Despite the efforts of the medical team, Dr. Salia succumbed to the disease. He leaves behind loved ones in both the United States and Sierra Leone, where he was born. Dr. Salia believed that medicine was his calling and pursued it because he firmly believed it was God's will for him. His passing serves as a reminder of the human toll of Ebola and the ongoing need to address the epidemic at its source.